                    "company": "University of Cambridge",
                    "description": "Project Title: Layering, Irreversible Mixing, Instability and Turbulence in the World\u2019s Oceans\nFully funded studentship from the Cambridge Earth System Science DTP\n\nI used the open source, parallelized Fortran code Diablo to perform idealised direct numerical simulations that inform mixing properties of oceanographic flows. By studying the energy properties of shear instabilities, internal gravity waves, and forced stratified turbulence, I improved our understanding of the relative importance of local shear and convective processes in the transport of tracers through the ocean.\n\nSupervisors: Prof. Colm-cille P. Caulfield, Dr. John R. Taylor",
